1️⃣ DEPLOYMENT WITH RESOURCE REQUESTS & LIMITS

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: nginx-deployment
spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: nginx
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: nginx
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: nginx
        image: nginx:1.28
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: "100m"
            memory: "128Mi"
          limits:
            cpu: "250m"
            memory: "256Mi"

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2️⃣ HORIZONTAL POD AUTOSCALER (HPA)

apiVersion: autoscaling/v2
kind: HorizontalPodAutoscaler
metadata:
  name: nginx-hpa
spec:
  scaleTargetRef:
    apiVersion: apps/v1
    kind: Deployment
    name: nginx-deployment
  minReplicas: 2
  maxReplicas: 10
  metrics:
  - type: Resource
    resource:
      name: cpu
      target:
        type: Utilization
        averageUtilization: 70

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3️⃣ VERTICAL POD AUTOSCALER (VPA)

apiVersion: autoscaling.k8s.io/v1
kind: VerticalPodAutoscaler
metadata:
  name: nginx-vpa
spec:
  targetRef:
    apiVersion: apps/v1
    kind: Deployment
    name: nginx-deployment
  updatePolicy:
    updateMode: "Auto"
  resourcePolicy:
    containerPolicies:
    - containerName: nginx
      minAllowed:
        cpu: 100m
        memory: 128Mi
      maxAllowed:
        cpu: 500m
        memory: 512Mi
      controlledResources: ["cpu","memory"]

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔥 What This HPA Does

If CPU usage exceeds 70%
→ Kubernetes automatically increases pod count

Example:

2 Pods → 4 Pods → 6 Pods

depending on load.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔥 What This VPA Does

If application needs more CPU/Memory:
→ Kubernetes automatically increases resource requests/limits

Example:

cpu:
100m → 200m → 300m

memory:
128Mi → 256Mi → 512Mi

depending on workload.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

⚠️ IMPORTANT HPA vs VPA NOTE

HPA:
Scales number of Pods

VPA:
Scales CPU/Memory of Pods

Usually:
Do NOT use HPA and VPA together on same CPU/Memory metrics in production.

