🔥 CLUSTER AUTOSCALER

HPA:
Creates more Pods

But if cluster has NO resources available:
Pods become Pending.

Cluster Autoscaler:
Automatically adds more worker nodes.

Example:
2 Nodes → 4 Nodes → 6 Nodes
when cluster capacity becomes insufficient.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔥 Cluster Autoscaler Flow

High CPU Load
        ↓
HPA creates more Pods
        ↓
No node capacity available
        ↓
Pods become Pending
        ↓
Cluster Autoscaler detects Pending Pods
        ↓
New EC2 worker nodes created
        ↓
Pending Pods scheduled successfully

Note
1. Install metrics-server
2. Install Cluster Autoscaler
3. Attach IAM policy
4. Enable nodegroup auto scaling
5. Add ASG discovery tags

eksctl create cluster \
--name my-eks-cluster \
--nodegroup-name my-worker-node \
--node-type t2.medium \
--nodes 2 \
--nodes-min 2 \
--nodes-max 6 \
--managed \
--region us-east-1
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔥 Super Important Interview Point

HPA:
Scales Pods

VPA:
Scales Pod CPU/Memory

Cluster Autoscaler:
Scales Worker Nodes
